  <section>
    <h2>Toggle Switch (data-switch)</h2>
    <p>Add <code>data-switch</code> to a checkbox for on/off toggle switch styling. Uses CSS <code>appearance: none</code> with a sliding knob. JS adds <code>role="switch"</code> for screen readers.</p>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/examples/demos/switch-basic.html"
      url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/switch"
      title="Toggle Switch Demo"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Toggle switch sizes">{{ switchCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Attribute</th>
          <th>Values</th>
          <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-switch</code></td>
          <td><code>""</code>, <code>"sm"</code>, <code>"lg"</code></td>
          <td>Enable switch styling with optional size variant.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Password Strength (data-strength)</h2>
    <p>Add <code>data-strength</code> and <code>data-rules</code> to a password input inside <code>&lt;form-field&gt;</code> to show a real-time strength meter and rules checklist. Works alongside the existing password show/hide toggle.</p>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/examples/demos/password-strength-basic.html"
      url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/password-strength"
      title="Password Strength Demo"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Password with strength rules">{{ strengthCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Attribute</th>
          <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-strength</code></td>
          <td>Enable strength meter and rules checklist.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-rules</code></td>
          <td>Comma-separated rules: <code>length:N</code>, <code>uppercase</code>, <code>lowercase</code>, <code>number</code>, <code>special</code>.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3>Strength Levels</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Weak</strong> &mdash; Less than 40% of rules met</li>
      <li><strong>Fair</strong> &mdash; 40&ndash;74% of rules met</li>
      <li><strong>Good</strong> &mdash; 75&ndash;99% of rules met</li>
      <li><strong>Strong</strong> &mdash; All rules met</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Range Enhancement (data-range)</h2>
    <p>Add <code>data-range</code> to a range input for cross-browser styled track and thumb. Add <code>data-bubble</code> for a floating value display. Pair with <code>&lt;datalist&gt;</code> for tick labels.</p>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/examples/demos/range-basic.html"
      url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/range-slider"
      title="Range Slider Demo"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Range with datalist labels">{{ rangeEnhancedCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Attribute</th>
          <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-range</code></td>
          <td>Enable cross-browser track/thumb styling and fill.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-bubble</code></td>
          <td>Show floating value bubble above the thumb.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-prefix</code></td>
          <td>Text before the value (e.g., <code>"$"</code>).</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-suffix</code></td>
          <td>Text after the value (e.g., <code>"%"</code>, <code>"&deg;F"</code>).</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>File Upload Zone (data-upload)</h2>
    <p>Add <code>data-upload</code> to a file input to wrap it in a drag-and-drop zone with file list display.</p>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/examples/demos/upload-basic.html"
      url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/upload"
      title="File Upload Demo"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="File upload zone">{{ uploadCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Attribute</th>
          <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-upload</code></td>
          <td>Enable drop zone enhancement on a file input.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
